-- Besix Wins $265 Million Contract to Build Bahrain Causeway, National Says
-- Zahraa Alkhalisi
-- 2010-06-13T06:18:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-13/besix-wins-265-million-contract-to-build-bahrain-causeway-national-says.html

          
          
             Besix Group, the Belgian contractor
that helped build the world’s tallest tower in Dubai, won a $265
million contract to build Bahrain’s North Manama Causeway,  The
National  said, citing Besix general manager Philippe Dessoy.  
 Besix and Haji Hassan, a Bahraini contracting company, will
build the 2.4-kilometer (1.5 miles) causeway that will connect
north Manama with the island of Muharraq, the newspaper
reported.  
